Polly, leave the outside edges until the next thing has been sewn to it.
Just mark the &quot;cutting line&quot; with your ruler and marker of some sort.
Then sew on the border if you are using one. (Sew with the straight cut
border on top.)  If the cut edge is to be the outside edge of the top,
without a border, then quilt with the excess part hanging out there &lt;BG&gt;
Then trim after you have quilted.
You will be sewing on the bias, but not having it cut will keep it from
stretching as much.
If you can, next time plan the setting triangles so that they are cut in
such a way that the outside edge is not on bias. &lt;G&gt; For the sides that
means using Quarter Square Triangles, and for the corners Half Square
Triangles. &lt;G&gt;

Have fun and don't worry about it.
Pati, in Phx

