The starching and the stay stitching , one or the other or both ought
to do the trick. If you want yet more stability, just sew some cheap
rayon seam binding all around, and then either whack it off when you
are done, or stick it inside the binding.  That flimsy bit of ribbon
won't add enough bulk to sing about, but it will  keep naughty edges
from wiggling.

